<P>
James T. Lynagh, president of Multimedia Broadcasting Co., has been elected 
president and chief operating officer of its parent company, Multimedia Inc. 
Lynagh succeeds Walter E. Bartlett, who was recently elected chairman and chief 
executive of Multimedia Inc. William L. Bolster will succeed Lynagh as head of 
Multimedia Broadcasting and was also elected a vice president of Multimedia 
Inc. Bolster was vice president and general manager of Multimedia's St. Louis 
television station, KSDK. Multimedia Inc. is a diversified media communications 
company based in Greenville, S.C. 
