<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORE MEDFLY SPRAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Here's one more taxpayer protesting the malathion spraying over our private 
property -- without our permission -- to benefit a handful of growers when it 
might well be harmful to our health! 
</P>
<P>
Over the years we've enjoyed fresh fruit from our tangelo, orange, lemon and 
grapefruit trees, knowing that they were not tainted with insecticides which 
permeate commercial produce in the markets! 
</P>
<P>
Now, after the recent overnight spraying in our area, we're apprehensive that 
lingering residue from this stuff might get on our hands and clothes while 
working in the yard. A performance like this might be acceptable in Eastern 
Europe, but certainly isn't here. 
</P>
<P>
W.A. STEPHERSON 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
