BOYS' BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
EARLY LEAD STANDS UP FOR SIMI VALLEY, 52-45 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SAM FARMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Steve Carnes and Mike Wawryk each scored 20 points as Simi Valley High nursed 
an early lead Tuesday to defeat Crescenta Valley, 52-45, in a nonleague game at 
Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
Trailing by as many as 12 points in the first half, the Falcons (6-2) chipped 
away at Simi Valley -- even getting within a point in the third quarter -- but 
were unable to take the lead. 
</P>
<P>
"We needed a 'W' against a good team," said Pioneer Coach Dean Bradshaw, whose 
team improved its record to 5-4. "Are we oiled up and ready to go? No." 
</P>
<P>
Nor is Crescenta Valley, as evidenced by poor free-throw shooting. The Falcons 
made just nine of 20 attempts. Simi Valley missed 11 of its 23 foul shots. 
</P>
<P>
BANNING TOURNAMENT 
</P>
<P>
Grant 72, South Gate 68 (OT) -- Rene de la Hoya and Billy May shared game-high 
honors with 18 points each while rallying the Lancers to a second-round win in 
the consolation bracket at Long Beach City College. 
</P>
<P>
De la Hoya made six of six free throws in the fourth quarter -- including two 
with 25 seconds left to send the game into overtime -- and May scored six 
points in the extra period. Grant (8-1) made 17 of 18 free throws. 
</P>
<P>
Jefferson 93, Sherman Oaks CES 81 -- Jefferson outscored Sherman Oaks, 30-20, 
in the fourth quarter in a consolation quarterfinal game. 
</P>
