<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 2 AREAS ON ROSE PARADE ROUTE SET FOR DISABLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two free viewing areas along the Tournament of Roses Parade route have been set 
aside for the disabled. 
</P>
<P>
One viewing section, provided by the city of Pasadena, will be along the south 
side of Colorado Boulevard between Marengo and Garfield avenues. Each disabled 
person can receive two tickets. 
</P>
<P>
The tickets are available from the city's Affirmative Action Department, (818) 
405-4216. Also available is transportation to the site via Dial-a-Ride. Parking 
permits for a garage one block from the viewing area also are available. 
</P>
<P>
A second viewing area for the disabled will be at a lot on the corner of Sierra 
Madre Boulevard and Villa Street. It is provided by Wheelchair Haven, a 
volunteer group, which will send two free tickets to each person who write to 
the organization at 750 E. Green St., Room 340, Pasadena, Calif. 91101. 
</P>
