<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
BREA-OLINDA'S MCDANIEL HITS SEVEN THREE-POINTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Aimee McDaniel scored 36 points and a tournament single-game record seven 
three-pointers to lead Brea-Olinda High School to an 82-59 victory over 
Freemont in the second round of the Santa Barbara Tournament of Champions 
Tuesday in Santa Barbara. 
</P>
<P>
It was the 32nd consecutive victory for Brea-Olinda (10-0) over the past two 
seasons. For Brea, Tammy Blackburn had 23 points, 12 in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
In the Cypress tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Marina 91, Los Alamitos 53 -- Melisa Sortino scored 32 points, including seven 
three-pointers, for Marina (7-0). Christa Yorke scored 14 points and Leslie Ono 
had 10 off the bench for Marina, which led, 57-23, at the half. Allison 
Arredondo scored 28 points, 20 in the second half, for Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
Mission Viejo 62, Valencia 44 -- Jennifer Rohrig scored a game-high 31 points 
for Mission Viejo. Sig Lo led Valencia with 11 points. 
</P>
<P>
Mission Viejo plays Ocean View tonight at 8 in a quarterfinal-round game. 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View 69, Millikan 33 -- Jennifer Sullivan scored 22 points and Tracy 
Wolfe had 17 as Ocean View (7-0) in the first round. 
</P>
<P>
In nonleague girls' basketball: 
</P>
<P>
Villa Park 47, Magnolia 38 -- Evonne Caouette had 18 points and 17 rebounds for 
host Villa Park (1-5). Stephanie Hill had eight points and 17 rebounds for 
Villa Park. 
</P>
<P>
Southern California Christian 32, Newport Christian 27 -- Angie Fetters had 10 
points to lead host Southern California Christian. Jennifer Rebal scored 23 of 
Newport Christian's 27 points. 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar 39, Laguna Beach 30 -- Viivi Vanderslice had 13 points and seven 
rebunds and Molly Flint had 10 points and five assists to lead visiting Corona 
del Mar (2-6). 
</P>
<P>
Dana Hills 42, Troy 17 -- Senior guard Joie Papa had 10 points for host Dana 
Hills (9-2). 
</P>
</TEXT>
