<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
TITAN WRESTLERS WIN FIRST OF SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton's wrestling team earned its first victory of the season by 
defeating host Portland State, 36-7, Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Heavyweight David Jones, who is ranked 10th in the nation and has a 6-2-1 
record, pinned John Paul Jones in 2 minutes 43 seconds to cap the Titan 
victory. 
</P>
<P>
Other top Fullerton performers were Jeff Maes, who pined Geoff Johannesen 
(5:38) in the 126-pound division, and Lyndon Campbell, who won a technical 
fall, 19-2, over Allen Rollins (6:10) in the 134-pound division. 
</P>
<P>
In another nonconference wrestling match: 
</P>
<P>
Oregon 20, Cal State Fullerton 15 -- Fullerton traveled to Eugene for a match 
Tuesday night. Jeff Mase (126), Martin Armendarez (158), Dan Henderson (167), 
and Jones won decisions for Fullerton (1-3). 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
UC Riverside 88, Southern California College 65 -- Kristen Bevis had 16 points 
for visiting Southern California College (5-3). Coki Drake and Becky Geeson 
each had 16 points for UC Riverside (4-4). 
</P>
</TEXT>
