<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AT&amp;T to Trim Rates: American Telephone &amp; Telegraph said it will pass on 
to customers, effective Jan. 1, about $300 million in savings next year when 
local carriers reduce fees for completing long-distance calls. Rates will drop 
1.3% for calls during normal weekday business hours and 2% from 5 p.m. to 11 
p.m. Sunday through Friday. A 10-minute call anywhere in the United States will 
cost a maximum of $2.50 during business hours and $1.32 or less at night and on 
weekends, AT&amp;T said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
