<P>
Imperial Corp. Has Negative Net Worth: Imperial Corp. of America said 
additional losses sustained by its already battered junk bond portfolio have 
resulted in a negative tangible net worth for the troubled San Diego-based 
parent company of Imperial Savings of California. Federal regulators have been 
fully informed of ICA's "capital deficiency" but there are no indications yet 
that regulators may seize control of the S&amp;L, ICA spokesman Bruce Dunn 
said. According to the minimum standards in the bill, ICA's core capital is 
supposed to equal at least $150 million, or 1.5% of its $10.5 billion assets. 
Dunn declined to specify what ICA's negative tangible net worth now totals. 
