Firm to Bring Accounting to Soviet Union: Ernst &amp; Young, a leading U.S. 
accounting and professional services company, has signed an agreement with 
Vneshconsult, a Soviet management consulting firm, creating what has been 
described as the first Western-Soviet accounting company, based in Moscow. The 
American partners will provide training in their worldwide audit methodology 
for Soviet personnel, Ernst &amp; Young said. 
