<P>
FORMER OFFICIAL ADMITS HE WAS SPY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former minister in the pro-Soviet Afghan government defected to the 
resistance and said he had worked secretly in Kabul for the guerrillas for 
almost 10 years. Pacha Gul Wafatar, recently the minister of civil aviation, 
was interviewed in Peshawar, Pakistan, after he fled Kabul. He said he had been 
advised by one of the guerrilla factions to depart the capital because of the 
possibility of a coup attempt. He was one of the most senior officials to 
switch sides in the conflict. 
</P>
