<P>
POLITICIAN'S WIFE JOINS ELECTION RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The wife of a Japanese member of Parliament said she is so fed up with the 
leadership of her husband's ruling party that she will run for election on an 
independent ticket. Makiko Hamada, 47, wife of Takujiro Hamada, a Liberal 
Democratic member of the lower house, said she has had enough of money 
politics, which have embroiled the party in its biggest scandal in more than 30 
years. The scandal, in which the Recruit Co. communications conglomerate handed 
out unlisted shares to gain political influence, eventually brought down Prime 
Minister Noboru Takeshita. 
</P>
