<P>
3 BOMBS FOUND IN DEPARTMENT STORES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three incendiary bombs have been found in major downtown San Francisco 
department stores since the holiday shopping season began, police disclosed. 
None of the devices exploded. It is not known if there is any connection 
between the three incidents, Police Officer David Ambrose said. The latest 
incident was over the weekend at The Emporium, where a bomb was found by a 
store employee in a box under a rug after moving a sofa in the area, police 
said. On Nov. 25, a bomb was found in a package at the I. Magnin store, and 
another was found on Dec. 14 at Macy's. The federal Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco 
and Firearms is also investigating, Ambrose said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
