<P>
BUENA PARK MAN ARRESTED IN STABBING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police arrested a Buena Park man Tuesday on suspicion of murder in the stabbing 
of an Anaheim man, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Anaheim police took Pablo Gomez, 25, into custody on the Santa Ana Freeway in 
Buena Park early Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Sgt. Fred Roush said detectives made the arrest a few hours after Gilberto 
Hernandez Pineda, 18, died from stab wounds at Western Medical Center-Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
Police and paramedics found Pineda bleeding from the chest in the 800 block of 
South Claudina Street, Roush said. The incident occurred around 3 a.m. Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Paramedics treated Pineda on the scene before taking him to the hospital. 
Pineda died around 12:05 a.m. Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Acting on a tip, Roush said, police stopped a vehicle driven by Gomez on the 
freeway after a two-hour search. 
</P>
<P>
"The suspect was arrested without incident," Roush said. 
</P>
<P>
He said police are still trying to determine the motive for the stabbing. 
</P>
