<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
GILLETTE CO. STRIKES DEAL WITH SWEDISH MATCH FOR WILKINSON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Gillette Co. said today it agreed to buy the Wilkinson razor and blade 
business outside the European Community for $72 million and will take a 22.9% 
non-voting stake in a company acquiring Wilkinson's EC interests. 
</P>
<P>
The seller is Swedish Match, which is shedding all its disposable lighter, 
match and Wilkinson razor and blade business worldwide in a series of 
transactions worth an estimated $672 million. 
</P>
<P>
Gillette said it will pay $14 million for its share in a new Dutch company that 
is buying the EC portion of the Wilkinson business as well as all of Swedish 
Match's worldwide match and lighter business. 
</P>
<P>
Wilkinson has about 2% of the U.S. blade and razor business compared with 63% 
for Gillette, estimated Patricia Klarfeld, spokeswoman for the American 
manufacturer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
