<HEADLINE>
<P>
DESORMEAUX GETS 576TH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAUREL, Md. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
World record-setting jockey Kent Desormeaux added his third victory of the day 
and 576th of the year Tuesday when Seattle Dawn claimed the $22,000 Marta Purse 
at Laurel Race Course. Seattle Dawn, the favorite in a field of seven, took the 
lead rounding the final turn and coasted under the wire in 1:45 4/5 for a mile 
and one-sixteenth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
